cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper deals with predicting the time to open an email, which is a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the social aspect of email communication and how it affects the time to open an email. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses the Cox Proportional Hazards model and mixture model approach to predict the time to open an email. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of survival analysis based methods for modeling the time to open an email. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with natural language processing in the context of email messages.
